<br>
Has the leveling curve improved?  It was brutal above 40 before.  Not to mention losing kill tasks above 20 was a pain. <br>
<br>
I did not like downtime between combats.  Has the new realm abilities mitigated this?<br>
<br>
In RVR, it seemed like two abilities dominated, stealthing and mezzing, has this been alleviated somewhat?<br>
<br>
I felt that the skald power consumption for the higher songs was not worth the value you got from them.  Especially snare.  Have they done anything to address this?<br>
<br>
I solo alot, has the new realm abilites and will possibly the new alchemy potions make this more viable?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whorde>whorde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/14/02 10:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=397.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Considering coming back - questions</span><hr size=1> nothing has been done to improve skalds directly.  we get no new spells or abilities, you're still stuck with the top snare which hogs power pointlessly, RAs cost a fortune in points and our unique RA blows goats, and now everyone and their dog has 30% to 55% body resistance so our DDs dont do jack.  add to that they lowered the # of points purge costs main and light tanks so you can't mez anyone really, even if you do it's only for 15 seconds with the top mez since they all have 50% body resist.<br>
<br>
however, downtime is now greatly reduced if you can find a shaman to give you endurance regen buffs.  &lt;cheer&gt;<br>
<br>
basically, you dont want to solo.  ever.  groups are now infinitely more powerful.<br>
<br>
alchemy ... no clue, we'll have to wait and see.<br>
<br>
overall, i'd not recommend a skald.  we get weaker each patch, and none of the problems with the class are addressed ever.  make a berserker instead, and find a skald and a shaman to play with.  you'll have a lot more fun.  if you do choose to make a skald, make a small kobold skald.  with you're speed you're very difficult to target in RVR.  being a troll i'm on the receiving end oftentimes of 4 of 8 enemies simultaneously.  even 50 points worth of RAs wont keep you alive long when you're taking 1200 damage per combat round.<br>
<br>
Phleet <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dane@teamskald>Dane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/15/02 11:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=397.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> change</span><hr size=1> It's changed some.<br>
<br>
Frontier XP bonuses for being near a keep your guild (or just midgard owned...less but still a bonus) owns.<br>
<br>
SMs out the whazoo with PBAOE (fastest leveling groups...how did we EVER get along without these??)<br>
<br>
Shaman with end regen non-con based buffs.  Get a shaman to give you this every time it runs out..they dont need to be in your group.  You can solo a lot faster when you always have full endurance...<br>
<br>
Celerity in healer groups.  Increases melee damage output by about 30%...quite effective when coupled with damage add, zerkers, and end buffs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Drops now that you can turn in for XP *even after level 40*.  FOr soloists, this is pretty neat.  Keep a list of where to turn them in and do them all at once.<br>
<br>
Increased XP from all quests..new post 40 quests (WW dungeon, etc.)<br>
<br>
There were some other XP boosts...but I think pre level 40? Somone correct me on that please.<br>
<br>
Getting 2PCs and starting a healer/shaman account is still the #1 way to make the game overall more fun IMO.<br>
<br>
============================<br>
All in all XP rate has increased some.  Mezz is less dominant in RvR (purge, determination, mezz healing!!, etc.), but it's still effective IMO, and running solo vs fully buffed infils is still a bad move....that won't change.<br>
<br>
-Dane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=albron>Albron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/16/02 10:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=397.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tyrantsonline.com/albron.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: change</span><hr size=1> I believe they changed the xp given for monsters in some way (not sure how).  In any case Mythic claims that level at level 45 and under is faster than it was previously.  46+ is unchanged.  <br>
<br>
I suggest finding a shaman friend.  Shammy buffs, with new end regen, is a serious cut into the xp grind (in your favor).  if you can, I did, find a supp specced RM friend.  That PBT rules.  A fg can do DF loop groups easy, without a healer, if youve got a good tank, PBT RM, and 2 shammies.  Of course a healer is always a great addition.<br>
<br>
Try to get into PBAE groups whenever possible.  the xp flows like water.<br>
